---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

import teamImage from "../assets/kenya-savannah-hero.png";

const founders = [
  { name: "Abdul", city: "Nairobi" },
  { name: "Huzaifa", city: "Boston" },
  { name: "Murtaza", city: "Ottawa" }
];

const values = [
  "Guidance that makes unfamiliar choices feel clear.",
  "The care you would give your own family's journey.",
  "Routes shaped by discovery, never by a fixed package.",
  "Stewardship for wildlife, guides, communities, and landscapes.",
  "Clarity around pacing, seasons, inclusions, and next steps."
];
---

<section class="section story-opening">
  <div class="wrapper narrow-copy">
    <p class="eyebrow">Our name</p>
    <h2>Soraya is the cluster that has always pointed the way.</h2>
    <p>
      Soraya Safaris takes its name from the Pleiades, the bright cluster of stars known
      across the Swahili coast and the Arab world as Soraya. For generations those stars
      guided travelers home and told farmers when the season had turned.
    </p>
    <p>
      That is the spirit of what we do. Kenya is home to us, and we plan every journey the
      way you would plan one for family: with people who are actually from here, who know
      the land, and who stay with you from the first idea to the last night under the stars.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section split-feature">
  <div class="wrapper split-layout">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Nairobi, Boston, Ottawa</p>
      <h2>A three-country presence is part of the care.</h2>
      <p>
        Being on both sides of the ocean means you can plan in your own time zone, with people
        who understand long-haul questions, family logistics, and the need for clear answers.
        In Kenya, the work continues through local coordination, route knowledge, and in-trip care.
      </p>
    </div>
    <Image
      src={teamImage}
      alt="Open Kenya landscape at golden hour."
      widths={[480, 640, 768, 960, 1280, 1600]}
      sizes="(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 50vw"
      quality={62}
      loading="lazy"
      decoding="async"
    />
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="wrapper section-head">
    <p class="eyebrow">Founders</p>
    <h2>Three founders, three cities, one conversation.</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="wrapper founder-grid">
    {
      founders.map((founder) => (
        <article class="founder-card founder-card--name">
          <h3>{founder.name}</h3>
          <p class="card-kicker">{founder.city}</p>
          <p>Co-founder</p>
        </article>
      ))
    }
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section values-section">
  <div class="wrapper values-layout">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">What guides us</p>
      <h2>We listen first. Everything else follows.</h2>
      <p>
        Before we suggest a single camp or a single road, we want to know who is travelling,
        how you like to move, and what you are hoping Kenya will leave you with. The route
        grows out of those answers. Then we take care of the rest.
      </p>
    </div>
    <ul class="value-list">
      {values.map((value) => <li>{value}</li>)}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
